      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (absolute hemolysis index) must be directly linked to the clinical decision threshold; secondary QoIs must be shown to be surrogates with documented mapping.",
      "rationale": "Absolute hemolysis index is the primary QoI and is directly mapped to the clinical threshold. Shear stress exposure time is used as a secondary QoI but the surrogate mapping uncertainty is not quantified. Achieved Gradation 3 against required Gradation 4."
